sentences: Robert Lissauer (May 1, 1917 – October 14, 2004) was an American composer, author, and musicologist.
Working as head of his own music publishing companies in the 1960s, Lissauer signed singer-songwriters Marsha Malamet and Judy Wieder.
A lifetime of experience led to his writing Lissauer's Encyclopedia of Popular Music in America: 1888 to the Present, 1991 and 1996 editions.
